I'm going to take one shot at saying this right and then I'm laying off this thread, mainly because I'm going out of town, but to add something to my previous post where I kept calling you &quot;the kid&quot; I figured I would address something personally.  Then again, I'd far sooner address the real human being rather than the character name, so in place of the above &quot;Kajinn&quot; please mentally sub in your real name.<br>
<br>
You've taken a couple steps in the right direction and you deserve credit for that.  Congrats.  I don't know you, but I've known some people who've gone through hard times in their past and although I wouldn't stack my own past up against some of what I've seen, I was a bit of a troubled kid too.  You could be a really good person one day.  I really think that.  These no-empathy he-screwed-up-large-let's-lynch-him-for-good dicks are direct examples of what it's like to grow up never experiencing real problems in your life.  You, at least, will never be that.<br>
<br>
You still have a long way to go.  Please don't ignore that or imagine it will be easy.  I won't go into detail about what was wrong or lacking in your post here (mainly because other people will be all over it anyway) but just remember it won't be easy.  Trying to get things the easy way (why work when I can scam!) is what got you in trouble in the first place.  It goes beyond gaming and is a life-philosophy.  You may not understand this yet, but part of the joy of achieving something is not just having it, but knowing you earned it.  And probably that's something you will have to learn.  All of these people unwilling to listen to you now (and some will *never* listen, some bridges simply can't be rebuilt) are just one example of how it's going to be hard.  Get used to that.  But it can and does get better.<br>
<br>
Anyway, for what it's worth, I wanted you to know that life is full of new chances.  Even if you can't fix what you've done in the past (and some of it can't be fixed) you can try to tip some of the cosmic balance by helping the next person down the line instead.  And yes, it really does matter.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
